Defendant Jamie Paul Buettner in court with attorney Mary Garvin Guimont.  Sarah McNutt appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
Case scheduled for Final Pretrial.  Parties have reached a resolution and proceed with plea and sentencing. 
  Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by parties.  
Court sentences defendant to serve 67 days  in the House of Correction with credit for 67 days, a TIME SERVED DISPOSITION.
Defendant to pay all costs, fees and surcharges.   Court ordered a payment plan in the amount of $50.00 per month with the first payment due on 08-01-2015 and additional payments due the 1st of each month thereafter.  If there are any missed payments any remaining balance will be due FORTHWITH and an immediate entry of a civil judgment is ordered by the court.
